         It was made to keep out mongol invaders, but was not to effective at doing such.  the great wall is not one great wall, but rather a series of great walls.  thus the mongols had little trouble going arround it.  in later dynasties the chinese put forts at regular paces so that signal fires could be lit if an invading horde was seen.  One of the more impressive forts built during the ming dynasty (I think) was commished to a gernal (I tried to look up the name but failed).  he thought about the plans for 2 days, figured out what sort of materials he would need. and put in an order for the exact # of bricks he would need.  his army, who was to help him build the fort implored him to make a back up plan in case he was wrong on the # of bricks it would take.  he finaly gave into thier pestering and orderd 1 extra brick.<BR>To this day on that fort thier is still one unused brick sitting above the main entrance.</P><P><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=11832" target="_blank">Bringer of Darkness</a><BR><a href="http://members.cox.net/umbrae/pic.jpg" target="_blank">Signature Pic PG</a><BR><a href="http://members.cox.net/umbrae/topless.jpg" target="_blank">Signature Pic R</a></center><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
