        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         There is one more reason that I belive the Great Wall was built. As we all know, it was built in order to keep the Invaders out of China as well as protect their land. The second, well you can keep people in China, even under great repression. With no where to run or hide, any would be heros would never escape into the Barbarian Teritories.</P><P>Now for my point, the third reason I belive it was built, it was also built for a quick transport of troops to isolated areas to repress attacks as well as keep the Chinese farmers in fear. See if word got out about them revolting, it wouldnt take long for troops the isolate the situation and eleminate those opposing the government. This would as well suit the High Lords in case some army did attempt to invade, causing the invading army to rethink whom they were trying to take over.</P><P>The Great Wall of China is still one of the best built "roads" to this day. Also it does provides China with pride of the fact the no one has even come close to constucting something of its caliber.</P><P>Just my thoughts on the subject,<BR>Velous</P><P>"Bad to the Bone"</P><P>"Pain and Misery; You shall suffer unto me."<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
